<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Only two records, both from the same area. The general distribution of the species is temperate, to the middle boreal zone. The Greenland records are both from low arctic areas. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. D. Orton; Trans. Br. mycol. Soc. 43 (2): 244" authorityYear="1960" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenogastraceae" genus="Hebeloma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hebeloma leucosarx" order="Ostropales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="leucosarx">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Hebeloma leucosarx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is missing from lowland regions of southern Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Beker, HJ" journalOrPublisher="Fungi Europaei Edizioni Tecnografica, Lomazzo" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B4" refString="Beker, HJ, Eberhardt, U, Vesterholt, J, 2016. Hebeloma (Fr.) P. Kumm. Fungi Europaei Edizioni Tecnografica, Lomazzo" title="Hebeloma (Fr.) P. Kumm." year="2016">Beker et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Grilli, E" journalOrPublisher="Candusso Editrice, Origgio" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B22" refString="Grilli, E, Beker, HJ, Eberhardt, U, Schuetz, N, 2020. Hebeloma (Fr.) P. Kumm. - Supplement based on collections from Italy. Fungi Europaei 14A. Candusso Editrice, Origgio" title="Hebeloma (Fr.) P. Kumm. - Supplement based on collections from Italy. Fungi Europaei 14 A." year="2020">Grilli et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Habitat and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Among the 28 species of 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenogastraceae" genus="Hebeloma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hebeloma" order="Ostropales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Hebeloma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found in Greenland, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Salicaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. leucosarx" order="Salicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="leucosarx">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">H. leucosarx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species that may primarily be associating with 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Betula" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Betula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Salix" order="Salicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Salix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the observations of 
<bibRefCitation author="Beker, HJ" journalOrPublisher="Fungi Europaei Edizioni Tecnografica, Lomazzo" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B4" refString="Beker, HJ, Eberhardt, U, Vesterholt, J, 2016. Hebeloma (Fr.) P. Kumm. Fungi Europaei Edizioni Tecnografica, Lomazzo" title="Hebeloma (Fr.) P. Kumm." year="2016">Beker et al. (2016)</bibRefCitation>
from Europe. According to their monograph, in Europe, the main hosts are conifers and 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Betula" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Betula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Beker, HJ" journalOrPublisher="Fungi Europaei Edizioni Tecnografica, Lomazzo" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B4" refString="Beker, HJ, Eberhardt, U, Vesterholt, J, 2016. Hebeloma (Fr.) P. Kumm. Fungi Europaei Edizioni Tecnografica, Lomazzo" title="Hebeloma (Fr.) P. Kumm." year="2016">Beker et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
); for the above records, the host is most likely 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. glandulosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="glandulosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">B. glandulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although in one record 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Salicaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. glauca" order="Salicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="glauca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">S. glauca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mentioned as present.
</paragraph>
